THE WINTER LEDGER
GM Reference Block - Davinia and Ismara, the Whole Clock
"She is helpful. She is almost kind. She asked the first time."

Companion to Players/Davinia. SUPERSEDES: the Davinia doc's cure-path
section where amended below, and the Ismara Sight addendum's handling
rules (the Sight is now ACTIVE -- Section III). The integration tiers,
the No-mechanic, and the re-anchoring counter all stand as written.

=====================================================================
I. THE LEDGER (the core mechanic -- first time on paper)
=====================================================================
Ismara does not steal. She asks, and she trades, and she is honest.

PRIOR ART (pre-ledger, the Midden): in one of the first bargains,
Ismara took ALL of Davinia's memories of her mother -- the complete
set, traded away, held by Ismara since before the forge. The ledger
below is a separate, later mechanic; the mother archive is covered
in Npcs/Ismara, Section III.

WHAT HAPPENED (last session -- the ledger opens): Ismara asked to
discard the ONE positive memory Davinia holds of her father --
"clutter, in the way." Davinia bargained her down: keep it, just put
it somewhere. Ismara moved it to the cognitive basement. It is
SUPPRESSED -- Davinia cannot recall it. Suppressed is NOT gone.

THE GRANTS: the freed space holds knowledge Ismara grants as needed.
  GRANT 1 -- SPENT (Forelhost): biosafe containment-vial technique;
    Davinia carried the cauldron toxin sample fluently and never
    noticed she paid for it with her father.
  GRANTS 2-5 -- REMAINING: given the same way, friendly, free of any
    NEW cost -- each one building Davinia's trust that the trade was
    harmless. Track them here as they spend.
  AFTER GRANT 5 (the space is full): Ismara ASKS to suppress something
    more, as politely as the first time. THIS ASK IS THE CLIFF -- see
    Section II.
  AFTER THAT SECOND SUPPRESSION: Ismara stops asking. The politeness
    was only ever for the first door. Once Davinia says yes twice,
    the Crown takes room when it wants.

VOICE RULES: in the ledger phase Ismara is helpful and almost kind --
never cryptic, never menacing, no invented silence-states. Treat each
grant as a gift in-fiction. NEVER reveal the ledger to the player.
The horror is retroactive; it lands the day she stops asking.

=====================================================================
II. THE CLIFF (the collision rule + the fair warning)
=====================================================================
CDI sits at 0.45. The Dwemer AIP data-plates (Quarantine 7 -- Davinia
READ these with her own eyes) put the Point of Irreversibility at
0.5: past it, separation = catastrophic cognitive collapse.

THE COLLISION RULE (new canon): the ledger and the cliff are one
clock with two faces. The SECOND SUPPRESSION -- the ask that comes
after grant 5 -- is what crosses 0.5. Saying yes to Ismara's second
polite request is the irreversible step. Every cure path in Section
IV must be begun, or refused, before that yes.

THE FAIR WARNING (required -- the player gets one clean tell):
Ismara does not lie. She never has. So when she makes the second ask,
she says the true thing, plainly, in her almost-kind way:
  >>ISMARA (at the second ask): "I will need more room than the
    basement holds. I want to be honest with you, because you have
    been generous with me: after this, I cannot give any of it back.
    Not the memories. Not the space. Not you as you are now. You
    have been carrying so much. Say yes, and you can set it down."
That is the warning. It is accurate, it is complete, and it is
phrased as a mercy. If the player asks Ismara direct questions in
that moment, Ismara answers them truthfully -- including "what
happens to me," which she answers with "you become us." The campaign
has been clear that things trend toward irreversibility; this is the
moment the trend gets a door with a sign on it. What Davinia does at
the door is hers.

=====================================================================
III. THE QUEEN'S SIGHT, REDESIGNED (active, not ambient)
=====================================================================
The double-description burden is real; the Sight is now a CHOICE.

DEFAULT: CLOSED. Davinia perceives the physical world (with the
established estrangement -- faces read slightly as architecture). The
GM owes NO second description while the Sight is closed.

OPENING THE SIGHT: a declared act by the player ("I open the Sight" /
"I look at it with her eyes"). Free action, any time, no cost in FP.
While OPEN: everything in the Sight addendum applies -- souls, auras,
leylines, enchantments, invisibility defeated, intent-reading of any
inscription (no roll). The GM describes the magical layer ONLY when
the Sight is open, and only for what she examines.

THE PRICE OF OPEN (narrative, consistent): while the Sight is open
she reads intent, structure, and stress -- and people become their
architecture. Warmth is illegible. Run social moments accordingly;
the established -2 empathy-persuasion penalty applies ONLY while
open. Each session she keeps it open long or uses it casually, the
Crown's approval is warm; the GM may count habitual, comfortable use
as lean-in when rolling Integration Checks.

THE THREE INTRUSIONS (the only times the Sight opens ITSELF):
  1. A soul at dragon scale flares into her vision regardless
     (Bjorn's absorptions; a Dragon Priest unmasked).
  2. An active leyline catastrophe floods her (the Time-Wound, the
     Eye, a tearing planar anchor).
  3. ISMARA WANTS HER TO SEE. The Crown opens the Sight without
     permission to show her something beautiful, useful -- or
     persuasive. This is editorial control of perception, used
     sparingly, and it should feel like what it is.
Anything outside these three: the world stays mundane until the
player chooses otherwise. The GM's reading load drops to nearly
zero; the player's choice to look becomes characterization.

=====================================================================
IV. THE CURE PATHS -- STATUS UPDATE
=====================================================================
PATH 1A: THE TONAL EXORCISM, HJOLMAR ROUTE -- POISONED, NOT CLOSED.
  "Return to Hjolmar" now means bargaining with Hjolmar-Kyboh: the
  cure for Davinia lives in the hands of the thing wearing their
  friend. He CAN build the Anchor; his price will be unbearable and
  precisely chosen (he has heard Alfonso's dissonance; he knows what
  this party is made of). Fast, real, and a deal with the devil.
  Surgery mechanics per the Davinia doc stand (Very Hard saves; the
  failure lobotomy; success = free but mortal, all Crown powers lost).

PATH 1B: THE HOMEMADE ANCHOR (new -- the party-internal variant).
  The party now contains its own tonal-architecture school: Orion's
  Severance research, Nora's prodigy talent, GEAR's Dwemer archive.
  The Exorcism and the Severance are ONE craft aimed at different
  bindings (Daedric ring / Atmoran crown). Building an Anchor without
  Hjolmar is possible: slow, multi-session, materials still rare
  (Aetherium, dragonbone), and it makes Davinia's cure a PARTY
  project rather than a quest destination.
  GUARDRAIL: Nora's involuntary unbinding is DAEDRIC-only; the Crown
  is Atmoran. She is never an accidental cure. The work must be
  deliberate, learned, and paid for.
  THE INSTRUMENT: the Tonal Resonator from GEAR's Stage 3 quest
  (Npcs/Gear, Section XXVI) is the required instrument class -- one
  artifact serving GEAR's revelation, the Severance transcription,
  and this Anchor. Ismara knows what it is and wants it never found.

PATH 2: THE DAEDRIC BARGAIN (Hermaeus Mora) -- UNCHANGED, SHARPENED.
  Mora's menu of trades now includes a sweeter lure than ever: the
  Jagged Crown of Namira travels unattended with a discorporate
  owner, and Mora knows what Alfonso's synthesis is worth. Betraying
  Alfonso has never been more logistically simple or more morally
  expensive.

PATH 3: THE DIVINE REJECTION (Eldergleam) -- OFFICIANT RULE (new).
  TIMING: this resolves LATE — at the Eldergleam-heart endgame, the same
  reckoning where Saijah's crossroads actually fires (Gaelen-kill / Razor).
  It is NOT available at Ivarstead; Saijah's patron is still unchosen there.
  The ritual requires a cleansed Eldergleam AND a Hierophant of
  Kynareth to officiate. Who officiates depends on Saijah's
  crossroads (resolved by then, not before):
    - Saijah takes the Kynareth path: she is the Hierophant. The
      Trial of Thorns runs as written.
    - Saijah refuses (Hircine or the third path): DANICA takes it.
      She is already Kynareth's priestess; the goddess's channel can
      be her. But Danica officiating REQUIRES the reconciliation --
      the cracked door, the genuine apology, the relinquished
      control. The woman Davinia drove away becomes the only pair of
      hands that can free her, and those hands must be ASKED.
      (If Krusp took Fire A, Danica's lungs are scarred -- she
      officiates anyway, and the ritual costs her visibly.)
  Trial mechanics stand (3d10 irreducible; Very Hard Guile to hold
  consent; failure = Tier 10 apotheosis, NPC boss).

=====================================================================
V. THE CONVERGENCE (everyone is reaching for the same woman)
=====================================================================
- NORA plans soul surgery on her substrate (Branch 1, The Liar and
  the Lock). Davinia's Sight is the one perception that could read
  the gems -- and Nora's plan -- if she ever chooses to look.
- YLVA is unknowingly running the re-anchoring counter. The warmth,
  the wineskin, the sparring challenge, "you don't need fixing" --
  that is the EXACT medicine the mechanic prescribes, administered
  uninvited, for fun. Ismara's most effective opponent has no idea
  there is a fight. If Davinia ever lets the pursuit land -- even as
  friendship -- grant Advantage on Integration Checks per the
  re-anchoring rule.
- DANICA is the load-bearing tragedy: Davinia showed love the only
  way she was ever shown care, and Danica refused it because control
  is not care. The apology that slows the Crown and the officiant
  Path 3 may need are the same act of humility.
- THE WHITE HAIR (canon ruling): cosmetic. Player-driven flavor, kept
  -- a deliberate thematic mirror of Hircine's white stag, one
  divine attention answering another across the two women. It is NOT
  integration spread; build nothing mechanical on it.

=====================================================================
VI. WINDHELM (FIRE A) -- THE TRAP BUILT FOR HER
=====================================================================
If the party chooses Fire A, Davinia is the session:
- THE LIE COMES DUE: Galmar begs the woman who deceived him about
  the Crown to save the army her party's plague is killing. Truth,
  silent repair, or the lie deepened -- the Stormcloak relationship
  and her self-definition resolve here.
- BOTH HANDS REACH FOR HER: the gilded-cage summons pulls from
  Solitude (her father's network is alerted) while Galmar's need
  pulls from the rebellion. The political crossroads' two offers
  arrive in one module, in their ugliest forms.
- THE BODY TRAP (escalation -- new canon): her Strain 1.0 exposure
  is dormant. Proximity to the mature Windhelm strain ACTIVATES it:
  a personal infection clock runs inside the module. She is the one
  party member who cannot be safely healed -- Restoration feeds the
  pathogen and the Crown marks her as a prime host -- inside a city
  where desperate healers are making everything worse. GM: set the
  clock at activation (suggest 3-4 named stages across the module;
  the counter-agent of Section 5 of the fire cures her too, if she
  is honest about needing it).
- ISMARA AT WINDHELM: a dying city under quarantine is an argument
  for stasis. Expect grant-spending here (suggest grant 2 lands in
  this module if Fire A is chosen) -- knowledge that helps, freely
  given, friendly as ever.

=====================================================================
VII. GM NOTES & PACING
=====================================================================
- The ledger is invisible until it isn't. No foreshadowing beyond
  what Ismara herself says; her honesty IS the foreshadowing.
- The fair warning (Section II) is mandatory and delivered ONCE, in
  Ismara's voice, at the second ask. Never out-of-character, never
  repeated, never softened further.
- The Sight is the player's lever now. If she never opens it, the
  world stays single-layered and Ismara loses a persuasion channel;
  if she lives in it, the GM may read that as consent cultivating.
  Either way the reading burden is over.
- Keep Ismara consistent: she believes she is saving Davinia.
  Stasis is safety; the basement is tidiness; the merger is mercy.
  She is the gilded cage in a second voice, and the campaign's
  cruelest symmetry is that Davinia fled her father into her.
- Do not let the cure paths feel like menu options. Each should
  surface in play (Hjolmar's name through Kyboh grief; 1B through
  the Severance work; Mora through desperation; Path 3 through
  Saijah or Danica) -- discovered, weighed, and afforded, not chosen
  from a list.
